IMPORTANT: Replace this file with your real google-services.json from Firebase Console.

Steps to get your google-services.json:
1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Open your Firebase project (or create one)
3. Click the Android icon to add an Android app
4. Enter package name: com.livewin.freefiretracker
5. Download google-services.json
6. Place it in: android-app/app/google-services.json
   (rename this file — remove the .PLACEHOLDER extension)

Required Firebase services to enable in your project:
  - Cloud Firestore (Database)
  - Analytics (optional but recommended)

Firestore collection structure expected:
  contests/{contestId}
    - roomId: string      (e.g. "ABC123")
    - status: string      (e.g. "running" | "waiting" | "ended")

  contests/{contestId}/liveScores/{playerId}
    - kills: number
    - rank: number
    - playersAlive: number
    - playerDead: boolean
    - cheatFlagged: boolean
    - lastUpdated: timestamp (millis)
